title: Double Door
description: The internal struggles for power in a family reaches such a fever pitch that a murder seems likely.

title: Merton of the Movies
description: A naive young man from a small Midwestern town travels to Hollywood to break into the movies, and through a series of mishaps and lucky accidents, becomes a comedy star.

title: Payment Deferred
description: Hounded by his creditors, a man in deep financial trouble kills his nephew, who is visiting him, and goes on a spending spree with the money.

title: January Thaw
description: A family buys an old farmhouse in Connecticut and find out that two of the former owner's heirs are entitled to live there, and will soon be moving in. Tensions begin to build until an incident occurs that may help to bring the families together.

title: Spring Green
description: An army officer and his son move into an apartment building that used to be a home. The son, a shy and withdrawn youth, has one overriding passion in life: earthworms. His obsession with these creatures brings problems for his father's relationships with the opposite sex, as well as his own.

title: There's Always Juliet
description: An American man in England meets a young British woman, and they fall in love. He is unexpectedly called back to the US, and not wanting to lose her, he proposes marriage.

title: Her Master's Voice
description: A wealthy woman moves her niece to her estate and away from the young woman's jobless husband, who the aunt believes is a shiftless, lazy bum. However, through a misunderstanding, she unwittingly hires the husband to work at her estate. Complications ensue.

title: The Man in Half Moon Street
To Dream Again
description: Shakespeare returns to England during WWII as a gentleman of the world and falls in love.

title: Ladies in Retirement
description: A retired actress lets her housekeeper's two older sisters live with her. She learns too late that the sisters are lunatics, and she's horrified to find out that they are involved in blackmail and murder.

title: The Doctor in Spite of Himself
Ashes in the Wind
description: An old woman's family is torn apart by her lingering death--and its expenses.

title: The New Gossoon
description: An adaptation of a 1930 domestic comedy by Irish playwright George Shiels (1881-1949), which had been performed on Broadway several times during the 1930s in repertory by The Abbey Theatre Irish Players on tour. A "gossoon" is a servant boy, a phonetic spelling for the Irish "gosún," which is related to the Old French "garçon."

title: The Bride the Sun Shines On
The Man in Half Moon Street
Letters to Lucerne
description: With the outbreak of World War II, a Polish girl, a French girl, an English girl, and two American girls are faced with the problem of living with Erna, a sensitive young German girl. When Warsaw is bombed and the Polish girl learns of the death of her parents, there is no concealing the feeling against Erna. The Polish girl had loved Erna's brother and he had been in a German plane near Warsaw. Soon Erna is trying to conceal her letters, unable to bear the anguish and bewilderment they cause her. Through it all the headmistress tries valiantly to preserve this kindly refuge where peace and tolerance may still have life. Finally, in a deeply moving scene, Erna is forced to read a letter which honestly describes her family's position. This letter tells of her brother's death: he chose to destroy himself and his plane rather than drop bombs on Warsaw. This absolves Erma and dispels forever the enmity which has displaced the girls' understanding and love.

title: A Long Night in Forty Miles
The Fire Below and the Devil Above
One Left Over
description: A man's wife and two sons are killed in an automobile accident, and he is left alone with his daughter.

title: The Adventures of the Kind Mr. Smith
The Man Who Took to His Bed
Charm Bracelet
description: An uninhibited widow asserts her independence from her children.

title: Patterns
description: Fred Staples is the newest executive in a large firm. He strikes up a friendship with Andy Sloane, the Vice President to whom he nominally reports. Staples is good at his job and the company's hard-nosed president, Walter Ramsey, is pleased with his choice. Staples has a crisis of conscience when Ramsey tells him that he's been recruited to replace Sloane, someone who has devoted his entire life to the company at the expense of his family. Sloane knows what Ramsey is up to but digs in his heels and refuses to quit. Tragedy ensues forcing Staples to make a choice.

title: The Diamond as Big as the Ritz
The Sears Girl
description: A Boston girl rebels against Beacon Hill tradition.

title: The Devil as a Roaring Lion
description: A young boy finds a wounded, dying man hiding in his family's boat house. The man, a prospector who has just killed his partner in a dispute, at first frightens the boy, but as the two begin to get to know each other, they become friends. Eventually the boy suspects that the man might not be all he claims to be.

title: A Night to Remember
description: A live re-staging of this episode, again with Claude Rains as narrator.

title: Bedroom Twelve on the Appalachian Waterfall
Flying Object at Three O'Clock High
The Girls Who Saw Too Much
Out to Kill
description: A young man searches for revenge.

title: The Murder of a Sand Flea
I Am Fifteen and Don't Want to Die
The Discoverers
description: The story of the discovery of life-saving insulin.

title: The Man Who Couldn't Say No
Angry Angel
description: A disturbed young girl is in a school that is set up to turn troubled kids into well-adjusted, respectable citizens. However, she finds herself locking horns with some adults at the school she is convinced are against her.

title: The Man in Authority
description: A Scotland Yard inspector is assigned to investigate the murder of a young man who, as it turned out, was the fiancé of the inspector's daughter. The inspector, however, has a secret - he is the one who committed the murder.

title: Three Plays by Tennessee Williams: Moony's Kid Don't Cry
Angry Harvest
description: Two young Polish men are arrested by the Communist authorities in Warsaw and thrown in prison, where they spend the next five years. They are never told what their "crimes" were and, in fact, are never tried in court. While in prison they wrote a book, and that is the basis for this episode.

title: Fifty Grand
description: A prizefighter at the end of his career is persuaded to have one more "farewell" fight for some big money. There's only one catch: gangsters are behind the match, and they expect him to take a dive.

title: The Outcasts of Poker Flat
description: A group of shady characters from a mining town wind up stuck in a blizzard with a naive young couple. The situation brings out the best, and worst, in everyone.

title: A Boy Called Ciske
description: A drunken mother and lazy, no-good father has made Ciske a troubled, and troublesome, student. A caring and concerned teacher and a handicapped classmate believe that they can help him turn his life around.

title: The Last of the Belles
description: During World War I, a beautiful Georgia "belle" finds herself being pursued by four army officers from a nearby base.

title: Killer's Choice
description: Investigating the murder of a young woman named Annie Boone, two homicide detectives are startled to discover that they are getting vastly different descriptions of the girl from people who knew her intimately--her mother says she wasn't very bright but her father says she was brilliant. A male friend describes her as a wild, carefree "party girl" type, but another says she was shy, withdrawn and retiring. The detectives set out to find out exactly who Annie really was.

title: Now Will You Try for Murder?
description: A television game-show contestant, who has won a lot of money, is scheduled to appear in an episode where he will be given the chance to win the show's $16,000 jackpot. Before the show goes on the air, however, he is found murdered.

title: The Eighty Seventh Precinct
description: A lonely widow is constantly calling the police to report a burglar breaking into her house. The police ignore her complaints until one day she is found murdered.

title: Next Door to Death
description: A teenage girl solves a "whodunit" murder game. Later she visits her uncle on the French Riviera and, buoyed by her success in the murder game, starts looking into a killing that occurred seven years previously, in which the suspects included a butler and a possibly corrupt cop.

title: Cop Killer
description: A cop is killed on duty, reportedly while breaking up a gambling ring. When the investigation focuses on one particular suspect, the precinct captain wants to immediately charge the man with murder. However, a detective investigating the case begins to suspect that the dead officer wasn't quite as squeaky-clean as he was being made out to be.

title: The Man Who Didn't Fly
description: A private charter plane carrying two businessmen crashes and kills all aboard. While investigating the crash, police discover that a third passenger never boarded the plane, and begin to suspect that the crash may have not have been an accident after all but a scheme by the third passenger to fake his own death.

title: Focus on Murder
description: A reporter sets out to investigate the murder of a Pulitzer Prize-winning colleague. He discovers that the man wasn't quite as squeaky-clean as was commonly believed: it turns out that he was a blackmailer, and there are more than a few people who had reason to want to see him dead.

title: Death Wears Many Faces
description: Two college students hitching their way back to school. A fierce storm arises, and they take shelter in a local farmer's barn. The next day on the radio they hear that the daughter of the farmer who gave them shelter has been murdered, and the boys are shocked to hear that a description of the killers matches them perfectly.

title: Death for Sale
description: A wealthy publisher has come to regret his quick marriage to a beautiful woman once he realizes she's cheating on him. He meets a man who can get rid of his "problem", and hires him to kill his wife. Afterwards, however, he changes his mind, and how he must find the would-be assassin before he carries out his assignment.

title: Night Cry
description: A tough veteran cop, expecting to be promoted to a supervisor position, is passed over, and finds himself assigned to a homicide by the man who took what he considered to be his job. His new boss warns him against using the brutal tactics he is infamous for, but the cop soon ditches his partner and pays a visit to the suspect in the case, in order to "interrogate" him--alone.

title: We Haven't Seen Her Lately
description: Elderly Aunt Violet lets it be known that she's particularly afraid of one of her heirs, who she thinks is greedy enough to do away with her to get her money. Not long after hiring a new gardener, Violet disappears. Her friends and neighbors suspect that she has been killed by the greedy heir, but her niece Helen decides to search the entire countryside to find out what happened to her aunt.

title: Web of Guilt
description: A loud, obnoxious former football player has alienated his neighbors with his boorish behavior, and also because they know he married his wife for her money. When her dead body washes up on an isolated beach, the husband is arrested and charged with her murder. Although he insists he didn't kill his wife, he refuses to hire the kind of lawyer who could prove it.

title: Back Track
description: An ambitious politician running for governor is informed by his wife that she's leaving him and getting a divorce. He tells her that, in order not to harm his chances in the election, she had better stay with him until after the campaign. When he arrives home one night shortly afterward, he finds his wife fighting with an intruder, and he is then struck on the head and knocked out. When he regains consciousness, he discovers his wife lying on the floor, dead.

title: Trick or Treat
description: A businessman, determined to let nothing stop his rise up the corporate ladder, neglects his wife and, in addition, is having an affair with his secretary. However, in order to keep up appearances, he refuses to give his wife a divorce. Complications ensue.

title: A Cup of Kindness
description: A new husband takes over his elderly father's hardware store, with the husband running the store and the wife taking care of the father and a somewhat dotty aunt who lives upstairs. However, when the father catches his daughter-in-law in a passionate kiss with another man, she decides it's time to get rid of the old man before he blabs to her husband.

title: Riddle of a Lady
description: A sophisticated, upper-crust British lawyer turns to a much shadier colleague to clear him when he's charged with murdering a somewhat disreputable woman.

title: Presumption of Innocence
description: A man on trial for kidnapping and killing a child admits to his lawyer that he wrote ransom notes to the child's parents, but steadfastly denies having any part in the kidnapping or the murder.

title: Three Plays by Tennessee Williams: The Last of My Solid Gold Watches
Three Plays by Tennessee Williams: This Property Is Condemned
